CHIKUNGUNYA - INDIA (04)
************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 29 Jul 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: India News [edited]
<http://indiaenews.com/2006-07/16586-viral-fever-spreads-states.htm>

A high incidence of a rare form of viral fever spread by mosquitoes has
been reported in 5 states, the minister of state for health and family
welfare, Panabaka Lakshmi, said on Friday [28 Jul 2006].
"High incidence of fever cases with arthralgia were reported from 18
districts of Andhra Pradesh, 27 district of Karnataka, 31 districts each of
Maharashtra and Tamil Nadu and 4 districts of Madhya Pradesh," Lakshmi told
the Rajya Sabha.
Lakshmi informed the house that 66 109 cases of suspected chikungunya fever
had been reported in Andhra Pradesh, compared with 543 286 in Karnataka,
202 114 in Maharashtra, 41 211 in Tamil Nadu and 43 784 in Madhya Pradesh.
She said the government had created teams consisting of epidemiologists,
public health specialists, microbiologists and entomologists for assessment
of the situation and providing technical assistance and guidelines to the
state.
Lakshmi also said that the states had been provided larvicides and
pyrethrum extract for fogging.
